    <div class="module">
        The arrival of spring means testing time for high school students: SATs, ACTs, APs, high school exit
        exams (in some states) and state standardized tests.
        <br/>
        <ul class="noHover">
            <li>
                Spring of junior year is prime time to take the SAT or ACT. <gsweb:articlelink articleId="244">Learn more about college admissions tests</gsweb:articlelink>
            </li>
            <li>
                Wondering what state tests your teen will be taking and how she should prepare? <gsweb:articlelink articleId="825">Get started with our guide to state tests</gsweb:articlelink>
            </li>
            <li>
                Students in 23 states must take a high school exit exam to graduate. <gsweb:articlelink articleId="1091">Learn about high school exit exams</gsweb:articlelink>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find out what students gain by <gsweb:articlelink articleId="951">taking AP courses and tests</gsweb:articlelink>.
            </li>
            <li>
                Learn about <gsweb:articlelink articleId="1160">test-taking strategies for kids with learning difficulties</gsweb:articlelink>.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
